This .gitkeep folder ensures that the empty SecondFolder is tracked by Git. 
Empty folders are completely ignored by Git and will not even show up as part of the repo on GitHub,
so adding this file tells Git that this folder needs to be tracked because it's important for repo 
structure, even if it doesn't have anything inside of it. 
Once you add actual content to this folder, .gitkeep can be deleted since Git will track this folder 
as normal since it is no longer empty.